# Data Model for Speech Coaching System

## Entities

### User
- **Description**: A user of the system.
- **Fields**:
    - `id`: string (unique identifier)
    - `name`: string
    - `email`: string

### Script
- **Description**: A speech script uploaded by the user.
- **Fields**:
    - `id`: string (unique identifier)
    - `user_id`: string (foreign key to User)
    - `title`: string
    - `content`: string (the full text of the speech)
    - `annotations`: list of Annotation objects

### Annotation
- **Description**: A suggestion for a gesture or emotion at a specific point in the script.
- **Fields**:
    - `id`: string (unique identifier)
    - `type`: string ("gesture" or "emotion")
    - `value`: string (e.g., "raise hand", "smile")
    - `start_index`: integer (the starting character index in the script content)
    - `end_index`: integer (the ending character index in the script content)

### CustomAction
- **Description**: A user-defined robot action.
- **Fields**:
    - `id`: string (unique identifier)
    - `user_id`: string (foreign key to User)
    - `name`: string
    - `mqtt_command`: string (the command to be sent to the robot)

### HardwareConfiguration
- **Description**: Connection settings for external hardware.
- **Fields**:
    - `id`: string (unique identifier)
    - `user_id`: string (foreign key to User)
    - `broker_address`: string
    - `broker_port`: integer
    - `topic`: string